{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":5391,"name":"","username":"buhb11","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/b/91b2a8/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-03-16T12:11:02.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôm very new to Urho3D and I‚Äôd like to start using it as my main game engine/framework for now on.But first I need to know if I can only use Lua whitout c++.Or only use C++ if I need something to be implemented.Can I do that and still make games/apps for android with only lua?Where can I download some Lua examples?  \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=5\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:04:13.296Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":152,"reads":42,"readers_count":41,"score":768.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":936,"topic_slug":"can-i-just-use-lua","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":181,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":5394,"name":"hd_","username":"hdunderscore","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/hdunderscore/{size}/1151_2.png","created_at":"2015-03-16T12:50:57.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eYes, you could use Urho with Lua only (eg, look at Bin/Data/LuaScripts, you will see all the samples are available in Lua), you could also use AngelScript and C++ as almost all samples are available in each for demonstration.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:04:13.494Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":13,"reads":42,"readers_count":41,"score":73.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":936,"topic_slug":"can-i-just-use-lua","display_username":"hd_","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Contributor","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":114,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":5397,"name":"","username":"GoogleBot42","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/googlebot42/{size}/62_2.png","created_at":"2015-03-16T17:16:24.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eMake sure you enable lua when compiling Urho3D because is isn‚Äôt enabled by default.  See here: \u003ca href=\"http://urho3d.github.io/documentation/1.32/_building.html\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttp://urho3d.github.io/documentation/1.32/_building.html\u003c/a\u003e This might be useful too if you are less clear on how to compile:  \u003ca href=\"http://urho3d.wikia.com/wiki/Build_Urho3D_on_Windows_%28MinGW%29\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttp://urho3d.wikia.com/wiki/Build_Urho3D_on_Windows_%28MinGW%29\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere is the lua documentation: \u003ca href=\"http://urho3d.github.io/documentation/1.32/_lua_scripting.html\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttp://urho3d.github.io/documentation/1.32/_lua_scripting.html\u003c/a\u003e   \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/wink.png?v=5\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":wink:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEDIT: You will probably want this too: \u003ca href=\"http://urho3d.github.io/documentation/1.32/_running.html\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttp://urho3d.github.io/documentation/1.32/_running.html\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:04:13.697Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":9,"reads":42,"readers_count":41,"score":53.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":936,"topic_slug":"can-i-just-use-lua","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://urho3d.github.io/documentation/1.32/_running.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D - Documentation","clicks":24},{"url":"http://urho3d.github.io/documentation/1.32/_lua_scripting.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D - Documentation","clicks":21},{"url":"http://urho3d.github.io/documentation/1.32/_building.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D - Documentation","clicks":9},{"url":"http://urho3d.wikia.com/wiki/Build_Urho3D_on_Windows_%28MinGW%29","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Build Urho3D 1.4 or higher | Urho3D Wiki | Fandom powered by Wikia","clicks":5}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":197,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":34386,"name":"Konradbeck","username":"konradbeck","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/konradbeck/{size}/2603_2.png","created_at":"2019-11-03T16:18:39.965Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ca class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/hdunderscore\"\u003e@hdunderscore\u003c/a\u003e,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou mention that ‚ÄòYes, you \u003cstrong\u003ecould\u003c/strong\u003e‚Äô but \u003cstrong\u003eshould\u003c/strong\u003e you?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhen does using a scripting language become advantageous?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf I wanted to design a game with many levels is this where a scripting language would shine?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOr when multiple versions were released, would a script be more beneficial if no new features were introduced?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-11-03T16:18:39.965Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":36,"readers_count":35,"score":37.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":936,"topic_slug":"can-i-just-use-lua","display_username":"Konradbeck","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1238,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":34390,"name":"","username":"JTippetts","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/jtippetts/{size}/357_2.png","created_at":"2019-11-03T21:49:31.845Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eLua is just another language. The main benefit it offers is essentially in allowing you to skip the compilation step, which can mean faster iteration time during design/prototyping. There is nothing keeping you from mixing C++ and Lua as needed. I‚Äôve found it beneficial to use Lua for things such as AI script components, while implementing performance-critical stuff in C++.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNote that there are still \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/issues/649\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eissues\u003c/a\u003e regarding garbage collection if you generate lots of garbage at one time, without interleaved GC sweeps in Lua. It can be mitigated by explicitly calling the GC when you are doing garbage-heavy things like iterating all the pixels of an Image or things of that nature, but it‚Äôs something to be aware of. Anything that returns an Urho3D object by value is a potential pain point here, so things like procedural generation of various things might better be implemented in C++.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-11-03T21:49:31.845Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":27,"readers_count":26,"score":45.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":936,"topic_slug":"can-i-just-use-lua","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/issues/649","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Lua: Objects not being garbage collected. ¬∑ Issue #649 ¬∑ urho3d/Urho3D ¬∑ GitHub","clicks":3}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"konradbeck","name":"Konradbeck","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/konradbeck/{size}/2603_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":30,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false}],"stream":[5391,5394,5397,34386,34390]},"timeline_lookup":[[1,2809],[3,2808],[4,1116],[5,1115]],"suggested_topics":[{"id":7074,"title":"First Person and 3rd person camera and water reflections","fancy_title":"Fir